race.comment: FORT WILLIAM (1) was well in commission last time but ran below expectations over 1580m at Clifton. Has been in the money three times over this course and distance, and two back he spaced the 65 graders at Gatton. Has a handy 2kg claim and can bounce. BLUE CHIP GIRL (3) was impressive last time at this track, scoring by 2L over this trip. She can make the quinella holding that form. PORRISTA (5) deserved her 58 win at the track and steps up to the mile for the first time. She's in good hands and has a 2kg claim today. This looks within her scope. Stablemate EXTOL (7) peaks and was better last time over 1300m as a firm favourite. Has a senior hoop aboard today and placed his only go over a mile. WHATJEUDOIN' (9) is better than the form line suggests and will carry a figure. Keep in mind.
